I have successfully implemented the core architecture and features of the AI-Driven Forex Trading, Social, and Robot-Generation Platform.

The platform is now ready for deep integration with your MT5 terminal and for the user to start training ML models.

üöÄ Key Features Implemented
1. Backend Infrastructure (Django + MongoDB)
Database: Integrated MongoDB using djongo, with schemas for Profiles, TradingAccounts, Robots, Posts, Comments, ChatGroups, and Messages.
API Engine: Built a complete REST API using Django REST Framework (DRF) covering:
Trading: MT5 account synchronization and order placement.
Robots: Automated backtesting and MQL5 code generation.
Social: Twitter-style feed with likes, comments, and group chats.
Analytics: Historical market data fetching and app visit tracking.
2. Trading & AI Core
MT5 Connector: A robust Python implementation to communicate with MetaTrader 5 for live account data and trade execution.
Indicator Engine: Custom technical analysis engine supporting SMA, EMA, RSI, MACD, Bollinger Bands, and ATR.
Backtester: A simulation engine to test indicator-based strategies against historical data.
MQL5 Generator: Programmatic generation of fully functional .mq5 Expert Advisor code based on user-defined strategies.
Machine Learning: Initial RNN (LSTM) model architecture using TensorFlow/Keras for future price movement prediction.
3. Frontend Experience (React + Vite)
Premium Design: A high-end Dark Mode UI built with shadcn/ui aesthetics, featuring glassmorphism, smooth transitions, and custom charts.
Component System: Centralized layout with a persistent sidebar and responsive navigation.
Feature Pages:
Social Feed: Engage with the community and market updates.
Trades Marketplace: Discover and follow top-performing robots.
Robot Wizard: A multi-step configurator to build and backtest strategies.
Trading Dashboard: Real-time MT5 account monitoring and active trade logs.
Global Chat: Channels and private group chats for trader interaction.
üõ†Ô∏è Next Steps for You
Configure MT5: Update the 
.env
 file in the backend/ directory with your MT5 Login, Password, and Server details.
Setup MongoDB: Ensure you have a MongoDB instance running (default: mongodb://localhost:27017/traderobots).
Run the Project:
Backend: python manage.py runserver
Frontend: npm run dev
Deploy EAs: Use the "Export MQL5" feature to generate robot code and compile it directly in your MT5 terminal.
The project structure is clean, the frontend is production-built, and the backend is ready for deployment. Just tell me if you'd like to dive deeper into any specific module!

